Aseema Kazi, the director and founder of The Style Factor, an image consultancy business, spent her holiday at  Ponta Do Ouro in Mozambique for Valentine's Day. They stayed at the Golden Beach Villa. She and her husband, Faisal,enjoyed some swimming, parasailing and the local cuisine. On her most memorable part of her stay, “The incredible warmth and hospitality from the locals was amazing. We had an incident where our car got stuck in the beach sand and within seconds there were a group of people helping with a smile on their faces “When we travel to Africa we are reminded of what a beautiful country we live in. Mozambique has been an amazing journey, one filled with peace and tranquility,” she said. Here are some of her memorable moments:   Parasailing was one of her favourite activities. 